locality: Around coastal lagoon 10km E of Mirbat

Yemen: Socotra, Nuged plain, E of Masgoba. Chamaephytes and psammophytes, heavily overgrazed; soil from estuaries with liemstone sediments and aeolian coastal sand. Alt.: 20 m. 17.3.1997, Leg.: B. Mies BM 665.

Yemen: Socotra. Northern foothills of the Dixam plateau, shortly after junction with Rewget track, Croton socotranus woodland, limestone. Kürschner & M. A. Hubaishan YP 4100.
